The paper proposes a new ensemble learning technique for classification tasks, which is a common topic in machine learning. The use of fuzzy k-NN classifiers and distance learning strategies suggests a focus on pattern recognition and image processing, which are subfields of computer vision (cs.CV). However, the paper also discusses the performance of the proposed technique on multiple feature real-world datasets, indicating a broader scope beyond just image processing. The use of ensemble learning and meta-classifiers suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG), while the use of fuzzy logic suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments also involve analyzing the collaboration among individual classifiers, which suggests a focus on data mining (cs.DM) and neural networks (cs.NE). Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DM, and cs.NE.
